{"id": "50550", "title": "Bug 50550: PropFind 404 error after MkCol success", "description": "Bug 50550: PropFind 404 error after MkCol success. This suggests it has to do with caching. Note2: This situation sounds similar to call 21288 (FIXED 'DirContext caching problem with Dreamweaver 6 when recursively creating directories'). Reproducible using a Jackrabbit client:

HttpClient client = new HttpClient();
String newDir = 'http://localhost:8080/webdav/output/' + UUID.randomUUID() + '/';

// Comment out this request to make the second PropFind successful
HttpMethod propFindMethod1 = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(propFindMethod1);
propFindMethod1.releaseConnection();

HttpMethod mkcolMethod = new MkColMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(mkcolMethod);
mkcolMethod.releaseConnection();

HttpMethod propFindMethod = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(propFindMethod);
propFindMethod.releaseConnection();", "OB": "When the first PropFind request is omitted, the response to the third PropFind request returns a 404 error. The access log shows:

127.0.0.1[06/Jan/2011:14:09:19 +0100] 'PROPFIND /webdav/output/f469e3d6e536407282dad989acaf57a2/ HTTP/1.1' 404 1084

When the first request is present, the response to the third PropFind request is successful. The access log shows:

127.0.0.1[06/Jan/2011:14:10:39 +0100] 'PROPFIND /webdav/output/81a97360ea4944d3b764d8c7e60e885e/ HTTP/1.1' 207 628

Note: After a few seconds, the response to PropFind for that resource is OK again.", "EB": "The MkCol request should be preceded by a PropFind request to trigger the issue.", "SR": "To reproduce:
1. Execute a PropFind request for the specific resource.
2. Execute an MkCol request for the same resource.
3. Execute another PropFind request for the same resource."}
